1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,350
[First, "My Amanto Idea" contest. The winner is Noriko Mach.]

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,033
Edited at https://subtitletools.com

3
00:00:04,350 --> 00:00:10,050
[Gintoki tripped on his scooter in the opening and brought it to Gengai for repair...]

4
00:00:11,860 --> 00:00:14,440
Oh, you fixed it up good as new.

5
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:15,460
You're amazing.

6
00:00:15,460 --> 00:00:28,570
[Mechanic's Shop]

7
00:00:15,460 --> 00:00:16,710
Piece o' cake!

8
00:00:16,710 --> 00:00:18,300
Who do you think I am?

9
00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:19,520
A wanted criminal.

10
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:22,210
You enjoy pecking at a man's wounds, huh?

11
00:00:22,210 --> 00:00:23,530
I'm just kidding.

12
00:00:23,550 --> 00:00:26,170
I'm getting you back for pecking at my scooter's wounds.

13
00:00:26,170 --> 00:00:27,530
Thought I'd dig into your wounds too...

14
00:00:27,530 --> 00:00:28,870
I was repairing it!!

15
00:00:28,870 --> 00:00:30,170
Thanks a lot, old man.

16
00:00:30,490 --> 00:00:33,600
Just the kind of work I'd expect from Edo's number one mechanic, Gengai Hiraga.

17
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,130
I'm glad you realize that.

18
00:00:35,130 --> 00:00:36,920
So about the payment...

19
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:39,080
Well, if anything pops up again, I'll be counting on you, Doc. Mechanics.

20
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:41,420
[Note: Spoof of manga Yoroshiku Mechadoc (Mechanical Doctor).]

21
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:41,420
Now about the bill...

22
00:00:41,950 --> 00:00:43,140
See'ya.

23
00:00:43,140 --> 00:00:44,290
Um...the bill...

24
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:49,390
Damn you, old man!

25
00:00:49,390 --> 00:00:50,770
You tampered with it, didn't you?

26
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:53,230
When the money gives out, so does the love.

27
00:01:00,630 --> 00:01:02,340
Hey! You all right?

28
00:01:02,340 --> 00:01:05,210
What the hell are you doing, involving innocent bystanders?

29
00:01:05,210 --> 00:01:08,360
If you hadn't booby-trapped my tire, this wouldn't have happened!

30
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,910
You okay, Miss?

31
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:11,120
I'm fine.

32
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,670
It was a minor collision.

33
00:01:12,670 --> 00:01:13,700
You're fine?!

34
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,010
But you're covered with blood!

35
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:16,620
No, I'm really okay.

36
00:01:16,620 --> 00:01:18,510
I really do need to keep going.

37
00:01:18,510 --> 00:01:19,490
Going where?

38
00:01:19,490 --> 00:01:20,780
Are you nuts?! No way, no way!

39
00:01:20,780 --> 00:01:21,930
The only place you're going is to the morgue!!

40
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:24,760
Hang in there!

41
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,970
My scooter...

42
00:01:25,970 --> 00:01:27,710
Just hurry up and give me a scooter.

43
00:01:27,710 --> 00:01:31,110
I...If I don't keep riding... If I can't feel the wind...

44
00:01:31,110 --> 00:01:31,830
I'll die...

45
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:37,040
What's with her?

46
00:01:37,830 --> 00:01:42,730
["For the Wind Is the Life"]

47
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:45,310
Noriko Mach.

48
00:01:45,310 --> 00:01:46,540
Born on Planet Highspeed.

49
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:47,820
Occupation: Express Messenger.

50
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:52,340
I've heard rumors about them, but I had no idea such an obnoxious clan actually existed.

51
00:01:52,340 --> 00:01:54,220
Don't talk about us like that.

52
00:01:54,220 --> 00:01:58,290
We are the noble people of the wind. We're honorable wind spirits!

53
00:01:58,290 --> 00:02:01,650
We are delicate, nymph-like beings that have to

54
00:02:01,650 --> 00:02:05,070
feel the wind at all times or we lose our bodies.

55
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:06,290
So what are you saying?

56
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:08,500
That you have to keep running all the time?!

57
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:11,560
Kinda like sharks that die if they're not constantly swimming?

58
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:15,900
No, as long as we're riding any form of locomotion like a scooter that allows us to feel the wind.

59
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:18,870
Running on my own is a bit tiring.

60
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:20,270
Go run on your own!

61
00:02:20,270 --> 00:02:22,450
Why the hell do I have to be your scooter?

62
00:02:22,450 --> 00:02:23,700
I...I'm in pain.

63
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,960
I'm sorry, but can you go a little faster?

64
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,930
Who do you think is in the most pain here?

65
00:02:27,930 --> 00:02:31,080
We can't make an injured girl run.

66
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:33,030
I'm almost done fixing your scooter.

67
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:35,450
I'm sorry for causing trouble.

68
00:02:35,450 --> 00:02:40,040
[Note: A famous song written for the TV show "24 hour TV, Love will Save the Earth." It lasts 24 hours and the song is sung at the end.]

69
00:02:35,450 --> 00:02:38,220
Since I can't do anything, I'll sing "Sarai."

70
00:02:38,220 --> 00:02:40,040
So you want me to keep running for 24 hours?

71
00:02:40,230 --> 00:02:45,190
Um, could you fix that piece of junk later and repair mine first?

72
00:02:45,190 --> 00:02:46,340
I have to go to work...

73
00:02:46,340 --> 00:02:48,280
Hey, what do you mean, "piece of junk"?

74
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:51,250
Your scooter was seriously wrecked, so it's going to take longer to fix.

75
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:52,910
Why don't you take his scooter instead?

76
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:54,680
What do you mean, "instead"?

77
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,050
That's my scooter, you know.

78
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:59,530
But can you ride a scooter with those injuries?

79
00:02:59,530 --> 00:03:00,590
Yes, I can.

80
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:03,660
There are people waiting for me to deliver their packages.

81
00:03:03,660 --> 00:03:07,900
Besides, this is my first job on Earth.

82
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:10,970
Someone like me can't get a decent job.

83
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:13,640
This is the only thing I can do.

84
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:16,290
I have to make this work!

85
00:03:16,290 --> 00:03:19,410
I swore to myself that I would become the best express messenger in the entire cosmos!

86
00:03:19,410 --> 00:03:20,590
Please put me down!

87
00:03:20,590 --> 00:03:23,740
I don't have time to be fooling around here.

88
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:26,030
You're the one who wanted the piggyback ride.

89
00:03:26,030 --> 00:03:28,990
I don't have time to hang out with slackers like you!

90
00:03:28,990 --> 00:03:29,910
Hurry, let me down-

91
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,710
I'm sorry.

92
00:03:33,710 --> 00:03:36,480
I didn't mean to make you help me with my job, too...

93
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:37,640
That's okay.

94
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,800
When you think about it, it was my fault.

95
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,710
So where to first?

96
00:03:41,710 --> 00:03:43,530
Let's do this quickly so we can get it over with.

97
00:03:44,050 --> 00:03:46,260
The wind feels so good!!

98
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:47,220
Try and stop me!!

99
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:47,580
Hey, you listening?

100
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:49,920
Somebody just try and stop me!!

101
00:03:51,710 --> 00:03:53,590
What the hell are you doing?!

102
00:03:54,580 --> 00:03:55,470
You're an idiot.

103
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:56,410
A complete idiot.

104
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,420
Hurry up and get on. This side!

105
00:04:00,510 --> 00:04:03,030
Don't stop! Don't stop!

106
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,960
I can't help it. There's nothing I can do.

107
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,680
Just hang in there. We'll be going soon, okay?

108
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,570
Soon?

109
00:04:06,570 --> 00:04:07,930
No! I can't take it anymore!

110
00:04:07,930 --> 00:04:09,560
I can't stand it!

111
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:10,510
Hey... Watch out...

112
00:04:16,370 --> 00:04:19,590
This is amazing, Sakata-san!

113
00:04:19,590 --> 00:04:22,170
The wind! We've become the wind!

114
00:04:21,860 --> 00:04:23,250
W-Wait. No... Time out!

115
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:24,810
I have to get off.  Please let me get off.

116
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:26,110
I so did not see this coming!

117
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,850
What do you mean?!

118
00:04:28,850 --> 00:04:31,120
We still haven't even made a single delivery!

119
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:34,660
I know. We haven't made a single delivery and things are already completely out of control!

120
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:37,410
It's like that movie where the teacher tells the students

121
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:40,520
[Note: Spoof of "Battle Royale"]

122
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:40,520
to kill each other at their school entrance ceremony!

123
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:43,170
Besides, how are you going to deliver the parcels if you can't even stop?!

124
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:44,630
Here we go.

125
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,790
One down. Next is...

126
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:50,910
You call that delivery?

127
00:04:50,910 --> 00:04:52,370
I call it terrorism.

128
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,540
The messenger...is late.

129
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:57,100
I'm pretty sure it was supposed to come today.

130
00:04:57,100 --> 00:05:01,220
My O-Edo squadron GinTaman action figure set, the JUMP free subscription gift.

131
00:05:01,690 --> 00:05:05,100
It's only while supplies last so if I don't get it now then I'll never...

132
00:05:09,790 --> 00:05:12,320
Huh? What's all this junk...?

133
00:05:12,690 --> 00:05:14,690
So what do you want from me now?

134
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:17,060
Calling me like this...

135
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:19,030
You and I have been over for a long time.

136
00:05:19,030 --> 00:05:21,200
You don't have to say it like that.

137
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:25,150
I just called because I was worried you weren't eating right...

138
00:05:25,150 --> 00:05:27,780
I don't need to have someone who walked out on me worry about me.

139
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:28,660
I'm hanging up.

140
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:29,720
Wait!

141
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,720
Dear...

142
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,210
Do you know what today is...?

143
00:05:33,970 --> 00:05:36,520
Oh no, never mind.

144
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:39,080
If you have no business with me, don't call.

145
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,260
Bye.

146
00:05:44,370 --> 00:05:46,690
Why would he remember...

147
00:05:46,690 --> 00:05:48,390
...that today is our wedding anniversary?

148
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:50,760
What am I doing?

149
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,700
I'm the one who walked out on him...

150
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:55,180
Excuse me! Delivery service!

151
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:57,070
Impossible! Could it be...?

152
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:01,170
Hatsu...

153
00:06:01,410 --> 00:06:03,140
[Happy Anniversary]

154
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:05,690
Here's to our tenth wedding anniversary.

155
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:09,610
So what do you think? We're almost done, right?

156
00:06:09,610 --> 00:06:12,520
Great! Only one package left.

157
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:14,700
If I may say so myself, we did a pretty good job.

158
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:17,120
We can't help it if some of the parcels were damaged.

159
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,120
Yeah, we did a good job.

160
00:06:19,370 --> 00:06:21,000
You in the speeding scooter!

161
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,240
Stop immediately!

162
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,210
Shut up!

163
00:06:23,210 --> 00:06:25,240
If I could stop, I would've done it a long time ago!

164
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,530
We're going to become the wind.

165
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:30,680
Huh? Hey Master Gin, what's up?

166
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:31,500
You on a date?

167
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,300
Oh, it's you.

168
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:33,710
I'm in a bit of trouble here!

169
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:34,030
Help...

170
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:35,220
Hey, he's a friend of mine.

171
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:35,710
Let him go.

172
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:37,510
W-Wait.  Help me.

173
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:41,570
Oh yeah, Master, this delivery date of yours looks like fun, but be careful, okay?

174
00:06:41,570 --> 00:06:45,720
Lately, there's been some terrorist activity by the exclusionist rebels.

175
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:48,840
They have been using messengers to deliver their bombs.

176
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:51,670
They have this vicious scheme where they make

177
00:06:51,670 --> 00:06:54,590
innocent messengers deliver bombs to embassies and such.

178
00:06:54,590 --> 00:06:57,130
So be careful, okay?

179
00:06:57,130 --> 00:06:58,250
See'ya.

180
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:03,950
Noriko, where does that last parcel go to?

181
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:05,240
The embassy.

182
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,690
Is it making weird noises?

183
00:07:07,690 --> 00:07:10,160
It's ticking. Like a clock.

184
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,580
I see...

185
00:07:12,970 --> 00:07:15,470
Hey, Sakata-san, what are you doing?

186
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:18,200
If we stop, I'll die!

187
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:17,540
We're gonna die anyway!

188
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:18,200
It's a bomb.

189
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,030
That's a bomb!

190
00:07:19,030 --> 00:07:20,560
Let's just pull over for a second.

191
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,590
We'll just stop for a bit.

192
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:23,800
When I get off the scooter, start running, okay?

193
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:26,940
I'm telling you, if we stop, I'll die.

194
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:28,090
Who cares about that anymore?

195
00:07:28,090 --> 00:07:30,290
I don't wanna die any more than you!

196
00:07:30,290 --> 00:07:32,740
So you're going to let me blow up alone?

197
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,330
I thought we were partners!

198
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:37,310
Didn't you promise me we'd become the wind together?

199
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,850
Like hell I did, you fool!

200
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:40,440
I hear when people die they become the wind anyways.

201
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,490
So let's pull over!

202
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:42,250
No!

203
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:43,580
I don't want it to be an explosive blast.

204
00:07:43,580 --> 00:07:44,980
I prefer a refreshing breeze!

205
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,860
It came off!

206
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:49,230
The brake broke off!!

207
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:49,220
Hey!  The handle!

208
00:07:49,230 --> 00:07:51,680
Damn old man, talk about a half-ass repair job.

209
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,280
Gin, Gin.

210
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:54,320
Come in please.

211
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:55,650
This is Gengai.

212
00:07:55,650 --> 00:07:57,010
Come in please.

213
00:07:57,010 --> 00:07:57,890
A radio?

214
00:07:58,050 --> 00:07:59,370
It doesn't seem to be working.

215
00:07:59,370 --> 00:08:02,240
I can't hear you so I'm gonna keep talking.

216
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:06,260
That old geezer... If he had the time to install this, then he should've fixed the damn brakes!

217
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:09,000
I forgot to warn you about something.

218
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:13,490
I should've fixed the brakes instead of installing that radio.

219
00:08:13,490 --> 00:08:13,990
That's all.

220
00:08:13,990 --> 00:08:15,430
It's just a confession!

221
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:17,240
Don't use the radio for stupid stuff like that!

222
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:21,040
Knowing you, I'm sure the brakes are already gone.

223
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:24,250
When that happens, you see a red button on the bottom?

224
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:26,910
That's an emergency mechanism activation switch.

225
00:08:26,910 --> 00:08:27,850
If you push it...

226
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:33,960
The rocket booster will kick in and give you a dramatic burst of speed.

227
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,690
So whatever you do, don't push it.

228
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:37,190
You could've said that part first!!

229
00:08:38,090 --> 00:08:39,500
The wind!

230
00:08:38,940 --> 00:08:40,810
This is no time to be excited!

231
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,810
We're the wind!

232
00:08:40,810 --> 00:08:42,120
I'll never be able to get off now!

233
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,690
What should I do?

234
00:08:42,690 --> 00:08:43,700
What should I do?

235
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:46,440
Edo's specialty, the traffic jam!

236
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,050
Is this how it ends?

237
00:08:48,050 --> 00:08:48,980
Gin...

238
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:53,680
Knowing you, you've screwed the pooch and activated the rocket booster.

239
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:56,280
When that happens, there's a red button inside the speedometer case...

240
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,460
Who the hell cares?!

241
00:08:57,460 --> 00:08:59,020
Whatever happens, happens.

242
00:09:02,050 --> 00:09:03,420
Old geezer!!

243
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:04,910
Damn it. I'll curse you from the afterlife!

244
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:09,600
All right!!

245
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,570
Sakata-san, we did it!

246
00:09:11,570 --> 00:09:12,360
We're flying!

247
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,140
We're flying!

248
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:16,370
Not bad, old man... Not bad.

249
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:17,380
I'm the wind!

250
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:20,230
Now we can fly somewhere safe and ditch the bomb.

251
00:09:20,230 --> 00:09:22,660
We did it!!

252
00:09:24,010 --> 00:09:26,890
Oh gosh... This is the first time I've felt such a delicious breeze.

253
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,120
Thank you, Sakata-san.

254
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:33,150
To tell you the truth... I...didn't think I had the confidence to make it in Edo.

255
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:39,470
I may not have it yet, but thanks to you, I feel like I can succeed.

256
00:09:39,470 --> 00:09:42,870
Even someone like me can accomplish something if I work really hard.

257
00:09:43,710 --> 00:09:45,070
Is that so?

258
00:09:45,950 --> 00:09:48,860
You may be right. The wind's not such a bad thing after all...

259
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:49,920
Gin...

260
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:54,870
Knowing you, you haven't heeded any of my warnings and resorted to the flight feature.

261
00:09:54,870 --> 00:09:56,570
But let me warn you.

262
00:09:56,570 --> 00:09:58,880
That mechanism uses up a lot of energy.

263
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:03,110
